**Bold** text emphasis.

***Bold and italic*** text for more emphasis.

- Bullet list item 1
- Bullet list item 2
  - Nested bullet list item

1. Numbered list item 1
2. Numbered list item 2
   1. Nested numbered list item

> Blockquote: Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.

`Inline code` with backticks.

```markdown
Block code "fence"

- Use three backticks (```) or tildes (~~~) to start and end a block of code.
- Language identifier (optional) can be used for syntax highlighting.
```

[This is a link](http://example.com) to Example.com.

![Alt text for an image](http://example.com/image.png)

Horizontal rule below:

---

| Table        | Example       | Here  |
| ------------ |:-------------:| -----:|
| Row 1 Col 1  | Row 1 Col 2   | $1600 |
| Row 2 Col 1  | Row 2 Col 2   |   $12 |
| Row 3 Col 1  | Row 3 Col 2   |    $1 |

**Markdown Guide:**

- `# Header 1` through `###### Header 6`: Defines headers from level 1 to level 6.
- `*Italic*`: Italicizes text.
- `**Bold**`: Makes text bold.
- `***Bold and italic***`: Applies both bold and italic styling.
- `-` or `*` before text: Creates a bullet list.
- `1.`, `2.`, etc.: Creates a numbered list.
- `>`: Creates a blockquote.
- `` `Inline code` ``: Marks text as inline code.
- ```` ``` ````: Creates a code block; optionally add a language identifier right after the first three backticks for syntax highlighting.
- `[Text](URL)`: Creates a hyperlink.
- `![Alt text](ImageURL)`: Embeds an image.
- `---`: Inserts a horizontal rule.
- Table creation with rows and columns, align text using colons.

This document serves as a quick reference to Markdown syntax, useful for formatting text on platforms that support Markdown.
